Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Stage I: Premature termination timing: This represents the last study week in which the teen started the week in the assigned arm (pre-PMT). Only available for those patients that prematurely terminated in Stage I.

Stage I: Study dropout timing: This variable represents the last study week in which the teen started the week as a non-dropout. Only available for those patients that dropped out of the study during Stage I.

Stage I: Premature termination or study dropout timing: This variable represents the last study week in which the teen started the week as an active participant in the assigned treatment arm. Only available for those patients that prematurely terminated or dropped out of the study during Stage I.

Stage I: End of Stage I Treatment switch flag. Stage I study dropout or PMT or final CGIt-I value > 3 considered to have not continued in randomized treatment arm at the end of Stage I for patients in the active treatment arm.
Notes: 0 = FLX, CBT, & COMB arms: Did not continue in randomized treatment arm; 1 = FLX, CBT, & COMB arms: Continued in randomized treatment arm; 2 = PBO patient

ElementDescription: Stage I - III: Observed Cases: Weeks from randomization to last treatment session date or assessment date based on premature termination/study dropout status and coded value for Stage I treatment switch flag. This applies to Stages I through III only.
Stage I - III: Observed Cases: Last assessment visit based on premature termination/study dropout status and coded value for Stage I treatment switch flag. This applies to Stages I through III only.
Notes: 3 = Gate C1; 4 = Week 6; 5 = Week 12; 6 = Week 18; 7 = Week 24; 8 = Week 30; 9 = Week 36

ElementDescription: Stage I - III: Premature termination timing: This represents the last study week in which the teen started the week in the assigned arm (pre-PMT). This is counting the true number of weeks from Time 0 regardless of Week 12, Week 18 or Week 36 timing.Only available for those patients that prematurely terminated in Stage I through Stage III.

Stage I - III: Study dropout timing: This variable represents the last study week in which the teen started the week as a non-dropout. This is counting the true number of weeks from Time 0 regardless of Week 12, Week 18 or Week 36 timing.Only available for those patients that dropped out of the study during Stage I through Stage III.

Stage I - III: Premature termination or study dropout timing: This variable represents the last study week in which the teen started the week as an active participant in the assigned treatment arm. This is counting the true number of weeks from Time 0 regardless of Week 12, Week 18 or Week 36 timing.Only available for those patients that prematurely terminated or dropped out of the study during Stage I through Stage III.

Stage I - IV: Study dropout timing: This variable represents the last study week in which the teen started the week as a non-dropout. This is counting the true number of weeks from Time 0 regardless of Week 12, Week 18, Week 36 orMonth 12 timing.Only available for those patients that dropped out in Stage I through Stage IV.
